{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01G6qW8Aj8YQQgTdicjmxYdG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The task is to build a wrapper class for reading from an SSH bytestream. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. A wrapper class for reading from an SSH bytestream\n2. Constructor takes a stream\n3. There's a method to read a fixed number of bytes from it\n4. If fewer bytes than requested remain in the stream, raise an EOFError\n\nThis is straightforward. I need to write a Python class that:\n- Takes a stream in `__init__`\n- Has a method (probably called `read`) that takes a number of bytes to read\n- Reads that many bytes from the stream\n- Raises `EOFError` if fewer bytes than requested are available\n\nHere's my implementation:\n\n```python\nclass SSHByteStreamReader:\n    def __init__(self, stream):\n        self.stream = stream\n    \n    def read(self, num_bytes):\n        data = self.stream.read(num_bytes)\n        if len(data) < num_bytes:\n            raise EOFError(f\"Expected {num_bytes} bytes but got {len(data)}\")\n        return data\n```\n\nThis is simple and straightforward. The stream object is expected to have a `read` method that takes a number of bytes and returns the data (or less if EOF is reached).\n\nI should write this to `candidate.py` as instructed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4674,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4674},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bbe21b94-100b-4d99-8a71-97069a0ee37e","uuid":"ca4f40ff-61f4-4683-96ad-98bbc9e2a14b","request_id":"req_011CbdNJMXaAcfvdyP2mHRwf"}
